description:
Move the canonical ToolCall representation to packages/messages. This is the provider-agnostic representation of 'LLM wants to call this function'.

## Location
packages/messages/src/ToolCall.php
packages/messages/src/ToolCallId.php

## Design
```php
// packages/messages/src/ToolCallId.php
final readonly class ToolCallId extends OpaqueExternalId {}

// packages/messages/src/ToolCall.php
final readonly class ToolCall {
    public function __construct(
        private string $name,
        private array $arguments = [],
        private ?ToolCallId $id = null,
    ) {}

    public static function fromArray(array $data): self;

    public function id(): ?ToolCallId;
    public function name(): string;
    public function arguments(): array;
    public function argumentsAsJson(): string;
    public function hasId(): bool;

    public function withId(ToolCallId|string $id): self;
    public function withName(string $name): self;
    public function withArguments(string|array $args): self;

    public function toArray(): array;   // canonical: {id, name, arguments}
    public function toString(): string; // e.g. 'search(q=hello)'
}
```

## Key decisions
- ToolCallId extends OpaqueExternalId (after instructor-dvk3 makes it support empty state)
- ToolCallId moves from polyglot to messages — it's part of the message domain
- Nullable ToolCallId (not ToolCallId::empty()) for absent IDs — null means 'not assigned', empty string means 'explicitly empty'
- No toToolCallArray() — that produces OpenAI Chat Completions format which is provider-specific; formatters handle that
- fromArray() accepts canonical format {name, arguments, id}
- arguments stored as array (JSON string parsing happens in fromArray/withArguments)

## Relationship to existing polyglot ToolCall
- Replaces Cognesy\Polyglot\Inference\Data\ToolCall
- polyglot ToolCall has toToolCallArray() — that logic moves to OpenAI message formatter
- polyglot ToolCallDelta, ToolCallIdByStreamIndex stay in polyglot (streaming concerns)

## Gemini adapter fix
- Gemini non-streaming adapter should synthesize IDs like the streaming path already does
- This is a small fix in GeminiResponseAdapter::makeToolCalls() — same resolveToolId() pattern

## Acceptance criteria
1. ToolCall is final readonly in Cognesy\Messages namespace
2. ToolCallId is final readonly in Cognesy\Messages, extends OpaqueExternalId
3. fromArray() handles {name, arguments(string|array), id} with same flexibility as current polyglot ToolCall
4. toArray() produces {id, name, arguments(array)} — canonical, not provider-specific
5. Gemini non-streaming adapter updated to synthesize IDs
6. Unit tests cover construction, fromArray, toArray round-trip, argumentsAsJson, toString, null ID handling

